RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 1 5F Dirt CR: 68. Claiming Purse 12500. (PLUS UP TO $625 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: BARSINVIEW lead the way from the inside, was confronted by an outer rival at the top of the turn, then inched away heading into the stretch, then continued to draw away to prove much the best in the end. RICHARD'S TX BLING broke outwardly and bumped rival, then raced in the back the pack while three wide, bid on the turn and was gaining ground gamely in the stretch and was up for the place prize in the end. DANDY LOU was bumped at the start, then chased the pace from the inside, was gaining on the turn, rallied in early stretch and was out bid for the place position in deep stretch and was best for show. JUST HANGIN RIDGE raced while two wide, then rallied on the turn to close evenly down the stretch. TWELVE PACK was in a hard drive to press the pace while two wide, was used up on the turn and tired in the stretch.

ENTRY.COMMENT: pace inside, cleared turn, drew off, gate to wire

ENTRY.COMMENT: broke outwrd, bumped, 3w, gaining, closed fast, up place

ENTRY.NAME: Dandy Lou
ENTRY.COMMENT: bumped, gaining inside, gamely stretch, missed third

ENTRY.NAME: Just Hangin Ridge
ENTRY.COMMENT: raced 2 wide, rallied 3 wide, turn, even stretch

ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed 2w, hard drive, used up, tired

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 2 1M Turf CR: 87. Starter Optional Claiming Purse 15000. (PLUS UP TO $3,000 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $6,250 OR LESS SINCE JUNE 9, 2021 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race At A Mi le Or Over On The Turf Since March 9, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Such A Race Since December 9, 2022 Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the Turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SKYKAT unhurried in the early going, settled in mid-pack for the run down the backside, circled four wide in the far turn while put to an early drive, responded well to the strong urging and took command in mid-stretch and held the closer safe. FOR FUN hopped at the start to give the field a length at the start, settled into stride under patient handling down the backside while trailing, angled wide turning for home and closed with a rush to be gaining late. CARPE HORSESHOE sped to the lead into the first turn from the fence, set a pressured pace to the head of the lane and kept on gamely through the lane although unable to hold off the closers. CARRY ON pressed the pace from the on-set from two wide, kept stride with her stablemate the entire trip and finished willingly in a good effort. ROZEY CHEEKS prompted the pace from three wide throughout, loomed up boldly in upper stretch and weakened late in the drive. CATO'S LADY tracked the leaders from the rail down the backside in striking position, was forced to sit behind the front wall of the three pacesetters in upper stretch, dove to the rail approaching the gap in upper stretch and failed to respond when clear. LIL ASHLEY B. chased the field within striking distance to the far turn and failed to respond when called upon. AFFICIONADO (FR) prominently placed from four wide through the first turn and down the backside and came up empty approaching the final bend.

ENTRY.NAME: Carpe Horseshoe
ENTRY.COMMENT: speed, pressured pace, responded well, not enough late

ENTRY.NAME: Carry On
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, between rivals, ran on, willingly

ENTRY.COMMENT: prompted pace, 3 wide, loomed, weakened late

ENTRY.COMMENT: evenly, no rally, no response

ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked leaders, saved ground, lacked room, lacked punch

ENTRY.COMMENT: unhurried early, rated mid-pack, circled 4w,long drive, gamely

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 3 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 60. Maiden Claiming Purse 13000. (PLUS UP TO $2,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Claiming Price $7,500. Texas Bred Claiming Price $10,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MORO FLASHBACK had shoe fixed prior to the start, set the pace along the inside, cleared the turn, then continued to draw away down the stretch to prove best in the end. LOOPY DUDE chased the pace while two wide, then dueled gamely with an outer rival throughout the last furlongs and was up by a head in the end. PRATHER chased the pace while three wide, then dueled for the place position with an inner rival throughout the turn and into the stretch, and hung in the end. GHOST CREEK raced between rivals in the second flight of rivals, then rallied on the turn, drifted in the early stretch continued to bid down the lane but came up empty. CAPO'S DREAM raced from the inside in the second pack of rivals, then bid on the turn before giving way in late stretch. HONOR THE LAW chased the pace while two wide, then dropped back at the top of the turn then continued to flatten out. ONEDRUNKNIGHT raced in three path in the second group of rivals, menaced on the turn then stopped. CAROLINA PARTISAN was unhurried early, then trailed behind the field throughout and eased.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 4 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 90. Allowance Optional Claiming Purse 36500. (PLUS UP TO $7,300 Open ATB) FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE OTHER THAN OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR STATE BRED ALLOWANCE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES OR CLAIMING PRICE $35,000. Three Y ear Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race Since March 9, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $35,000 (Maiden, Claiming, Or Starter Races Not Considered In Allowances). Texas Bred Claiming Price $40,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: FASHION RAGE broke alertly, was allowed to settle just off the pace, stalked the leaders through the turn, rallied three wide to take command turning for home and drew clear holding his advantage to the wire. MY FRIEND AMY reserved off the pace for the first half mile, angled out at the head of the lane and closed with a rush to gain the place in the final stride. TIFFANY TWIST tracked the pace from striking distance to the quarter pole, loomed up turning for home with his bid and failed to sustain his bid late. PINKY TOE pressed the pace from the fence for a half mile, briefly took the lead, was overtaken quickly by the winner, kept on to mid-stretch and weakened deep in the drive. RECLUSIVE slow early to trail and showed late interest making up ground in the lane. HEATED ARGUMENT went evenly failing to ever menace. TIPSY GAL sped to the lead from two wide, battled on the front to the quarter pole and tired turning for home. UNIQUE BABE was never a threat.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ATRAS bumped rival at the start, then vied for the lead from the inside, gained command at the top of the turn and was kept to task till the end. OCELOT vied for the lead while two wide, was in a strong drive throughout the turn, then continued to bid gamely down the stretch while holding onto the place position. GOZILLA raced in the middle of the field while three wide, then rallied in the upper stretch and closed willingly in the end. DECLINED was bumped at the start, then chased the pace from the inside into the turn, menaced in the early stretch and was closing well in the end. BI BI raced in the two path in the back of the pack, then rallied from the three path in the stretch but it was too little too late. WHOOPING JAY vied for the lead while four wide, then continued to stalk the pace throughout the turn before giving way in the stretch. TOTALIZER settled along the inside and was no threat. PRINCE RAMA vied for the lead while three wide, then dropped back before the turn and stopped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 6 6F Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Special Weight Purse 33000. (PLUS UP TO $6,600 Open ATB) FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 119 lbs.; Older, 124 lbs. (Preference To Horses That Have Not Started For $20,000 Or Less In Their Last 3 Starts).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMP CUSTER stalked the leaders from five wide, took the lead at the quarter pole while still in hand, was set to a drive in upper stretch and drew clear late. LOOK SHARP flashed speed to duel on the lead from between horses to top of the lane, dropped off the leader when passed in upper stretch and dug-in gamely to keep coming down the lane in a good effort. TAKE FLIGHT hesitated at the start giving the field a length advantage, moved into contention along the rail down the backside while patiently handled, angled out in mid-stretch and kept on well to gain the show. SMOKEY STORY pressed the pace from the rail in a three horse duel, loomed in upper stretch and ran-on well to just miss the show in a blanket photo. JUST BATTLE trailed early on, found his best stride late to be gaining belatedly down the stretch. GOLD BARON raced in mid-pack within striking distance to the top of the lane and failed to close ground coming home. COMO ESTAS prominently placed for the first quarter mile, dropped back into the turn and posed no threat. PONZA flashed speed for the first quarter to press the pace from three wide and faded leaving the three-eighths pole.

Claiming Price $5,000. Texas Bred Claiming Price $6,250.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: POMEROY HAZE tracked the pace while two wide, was urging steadily on the turn to rally in the early stretch, then edged clear in the final furlong and was up in the final strides to prevail. LOOKIN HIGH tracked the pace from the inside under a steady hand ride, then bid on the turn, angled out three wide in the early stretch and closed belatedly in the end. BEHIND THE CURTAIN set the pace along the inside, was in a long drive heading into the home stretch but was out bid in the end by outer foes and was best for the show prize. LOUIS LE GRANDE raced in the middle of the field from the inside, was in a steady drive on the turn, rallied in the early stretch and closed well in the end. FRA MAURO stalked the pace while two wide, then menaced on the turn to try and catch the leader but flattened out in the stretch. GOLD ACCOUNT raced along the inside towards the back of the pack, made a mild bid on the turn from the three path but needed more in the end. GUNNER PAUL was bumped at the start, then raced in the middle of the pack while two wide, was urging on the turn to rally in mid stretch but came up empty in the end. HE'S PRETTY LUCKY raced behind most of the field while three wide, then rallied on the turn and was no threat. OJITOS settled in the three path down the backstretch, then bid on the turn and flattened out in the stretch and was no threat. PEPPERMAN was unhurried early then raced behind the field along the inside and needed rally in the end. PRINCIPE GUILHERME raced in the middle of the field while four wide, then faded throughout and was no rally. EPIC RUN was in a hard drive while racing from the five path in the middle of the pack, came out nine to ten wide in the upper stretch and was no threat.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: LONE STAR PARK RACE 8 7 1/2F Turf CR: 72. Allowance Purse 33500. (PLUS UP TO $1,675 Open ATB) FOR TEXAS ACCREDITED FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON A RACE OTHER THAN MAIDEN, CLAIMING, STARTER, OR TRIAL OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 118 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Non-wi nners Of A Race Since April 9, 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. (If Deemed inadvisable by management to run this race over the turf course, it will be run on the main track at One Mile. If the race is for two year olds, it will be run at Seven Furlongs.) (Rail at 20 feet).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: XTRA SPICY stalked the pace from two wide in the second flight, moved to challenge in the turn, took the lead in mid-stretch under strong handling and kicked clear late. MISSINGYOUCRAZY pressed the pace from two wide into the first turn and down the backstretch, moved to the lead at the quarter pole and continued well to the wire but failed to hold off the winner in a good try. HAILEY'S JEWEL unhurried for the first half mile, rallied four wide on the final bend to loom boldly in upper stretch but failed to sustain her bid late in the drive. WICKED SONG well positioned in the clear down the backside, moved to contention turning for home and lacked a closing kick. COUNTRY JEWEL went evenly and failed to gain on the leaders. ITS A GEE THING prominently placed for the first three quarters along the fence but lacked a response when called upon for the drive. KAUSE I'M DEVINE bumped at the start, dropped to the rear through the first turn and down the backside, continuously raced up to be on heels and taken in hand, rallied wide in the far turn and flattened out coming for home. QUEEN OF BEERS sped to the lead into the first turn and set a pressured pace for a half mile and came up empty.
